supportDesc.extent: iii, 294, iii leaves : 161 x 102 (115 x 65) mm, bound to 162 x 110 mm

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Written in naskh in black ink; pointed, vocalized.

decoDesc.decoNote: Double page illuminated first opening in blue and gold with red and blue finials and text on cloudbands (f. 1v-2r); gold, slightly lobed circular medallions divided into six sections mark verse endings; medallions of gold, light blue, and red in several shapes including teardrop, sun, and star-shape in the margins mark section divisions; sūrah headings are white ink on a gold cartouche with foliate fill around the ends in gold and red; readings in red.

binding.p: Brown leather over pasteboard with flap (detached); gold-tooled diaper grid of squares made of double arrow patterns with central dots surround by a double frame; bright yellow embossed paper doublure.

origin.p: Copy completed on 11 Jumādá al-Ākhirah 1224 AH (12 July 1809) by Muṣṭafá Rifqī, a student of al-Sayyid ʻUthmān, al-maʻrūf bi-Dāmād Ibrāhīm al-ʻAfīf (f. 294r).

history.provenance: Gift of Harry G. Friedman (library donation bookplate inside front cover).
